  "Allegations" : "SEC LITIGATION RELEASE 22983/APRIL 30, 2014: THE SEC FILED SECURITIES FRAUD CHARGES AGAINST BARRY R. BEKKEDAM ALLEGING THAT FROM APRIL THROUGH OCTOBER 2009, BEKKEDAM FRAUDULENTLY INDUCED, OR ASSISTED IN INDUCING, HIS ADVISORY CLIENTS AND OTHERS TO INVEST APPROXIMATELY $100 MILLION IN A FUND THAT PURPORTEDLY PURCHASED LAWSUIT SETTLEMENTS FROM A NOW-CONVICTED PONZI-SCHEMER. BEKKEDAM AND A BUSINESSMAN FORMED A PRIVATE FUND TO ENABLE BEKKEDAM TO RAISE FUNDS FROM CLIENTS AND OTHERS TO BE INVESTED EXCLUSIVELY IN SETTLEMENTS SOLD BY THE PONZI-SCHEMER. THE SEC ALLEGES THAT WHEN SOLICITING HIS ADVISORY CLIENTS AND OTHER PROSPECTIVE INVESTORS TO INVEST IN THE FUND, BEKKEDAM MADE MATERIAL MISREPRESENTATIONS AND OMISSIONS REGARDING THE LEVEL OF DUE DILIGENCE HE AND HIS INVESTMENT ADVISER HAD PERFORMED, INCLUDING THEIR ACCESS TO INFORMATION CONFIRMING THE EXISTENCE OF THE SETTLEMENT FUNDS, THE AUTHENTICITY OF THE INVESTMENT PROGRAM, AND THE OVERALL SAFETY OF INVESTING IN THE SETTLEMENTS. AT THE TIME THAT THE SCHEME COLLAPSED, FUND INVESTORS HAD RECEIVED APPROXIMATELY $2 MILLION IN INTEREST PAYMENTS, WITH THEIR APPROXIMATELY $100 MILLION PRINCIPAL INVESTMENTS LOST IN THE PONZI SCHEME. BEKKEDAM ALSO CONCEALED FROM HIS ADVISORY CLIENTS AND OTHER PROSPECTIVE INVESTORS THE NATURE OF HIS RELATIONSHIP WITH THE BUSINESSMAN AND THE CLEAR CONFLICTS OF INTEREST RESULTING FROM THE FINANCIAL ARRANGEMENTS BETWEEN BEKKEDAM AND THE BUSINESSMAN AND HIS AFFILIATES. THROUGHOUT 2009, BEKKEDAM AND THE BUSINESSMAN ENGAGED IN A SERIES OF TRANSACTIONS DESIGNED TO FUNNEL MONEY TO BEKKEDAM AND HIS RELATED ENTITIES IN EXCHANGE FOR BEKKEDAM'S SOLICITATION OF INVESTORS IN THE FUND. THE COMPLAINT ALLEGES THAT BEKKEDAM VIOLATED SECTION 17(A)(2) OF THE SECURITIES ACT OF 1933, SECTION 10(B) OF THE SECURITIES EXCHANGE ACT OF 1934 AND RULE 10B-5(B) THEREUNDER, AND SECTIONS 206(1) AND 206(2) OF THE INVESTMENT ADVISERS ACT OF 1940.",
